r419 | poftwaresatent | 2006-12-12 09:24:07 -0800 (Tue, 12 Dec 2006) | 7 lines

The new gplan/TraversabilityMapCS depends on estar.sourceforge.net and
this has to be properly taken into account during configure time: if
you specify --with-estar (or --with-estar=PATH) on your configure
command line, this code will be included in your built of
libsunflower. These changes showed the deficiency of autogen.sh, which
was replaced by bootstrap-buildsystem.sh.

