------------------------------------------------------------------------
r612 | poftwaresatent | 2007-05-19 03:21:46 -0700 (Sat, 19 May 2007) | 17 lines

Added expo::MotionPlanner::ManualStop() and ManualResume(), which
allows users to halt the robot while it is executing normal path
following behavior, and later resume the path to the same goal.

Also made a refactoring of the expo::MotionPlanner state machine,
because the NullState was replaced by ManualStopState and I grabbed
the opportunity to clean up some old crufty code. It's still not
spotless, but at least now most of the dirty stuff lives within the
new expo::MotioPlannerStateMachine class, which is defined in
expo/MotionPlannerState.{h,c}pp.

Note that the cwrap/expo.h was extended: the new
EXPO_CWRAP_MANUAL_STOP value was added to the enum
EXPO_CWRAP_STATE_ID, so you might have to update your C-wrapper client
code. I kept the EXPO_CWRAP_NULL value in there, even though it will
never be returned, just to break fewer old code.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r615 | poftwaresatent | 2007-05-19 10:04:34 -0700 (Sat, 19 May 2007) | 4 lines

